1
00:00:30,730 --> 00:00:32,740
-Is that the last one?
-Yes.

2
00:00:38,280 --> 00:00:41,870
I doubt Ketil's side has any will
to continue fighting.

3
00:00:42,660 --> 00:00:46,000
I will send another messenger
to urge them to surrender.

4
00:00:46,790 --> 00:00:47,830
Your Majesty.

5
00:00:49,710 --> 00:00:53,340
May we seize the houses on the farm?

6
00:00:54,010 --> 00:00:57,930
My soldiers do not like
camping out in tents.

7
00:00:58,010 --> 00:00:59,010
You may not.

8
00:00:59,680 --> 00:01:03,600
I forbid anyone from stepping foot
on the farm.

9
00:01:04,350 --> 00:01:07,230
Once the soldiers get in,
they will begin pillaging.

10
00:01:07,810 --> 00:01:10,730
Pillaging is a right given to the victors.

11
00:01:11,320 --> 00:01:15,450
The purpose of this battle
is the requisition of the entire farm.

12
00:01:15,530 --> 00:01:17,110
Not pillaging.

13
00:01:18,490 --> 00:01:23,580
I will give the Jomsvikings
a generous reward myself.

14
00:01:26,540 --> 00:01:27,920
As you wish.

15
00:01:39,390 --> 00:01:44,640
Isn't it a little too late
to show mercy, Canute?

16
00:01:46,390 --> 00:01:52,230
You are doing the right thing.
This is the job of a king.

17
00:01:53,270 --> 00:01:58,400
For the sake of the bigger purpose,
you must save those you must save

18
00:01:58,490 --> 00:02:01,320
and kill those you must kill.

19
00:02:01,990 --> 00:02:05,200
Common people cannot shoulder this burden.

20
00:02:06,410 --> 00:02:11,540
I am still in hell,
far away from paradise.

21
00:02:11,630 --> 00:02:15,460
Hell has its own laws.

22
00:02:16,760 --> 00:02:18,630
Canute,

23
00:02:19,510 --> 00:02:24,060
you killed your father,
you killed your brother,

24
00:02:24,140 --> 00:02:27,770
and you will have to
continue killing until

25
00:02:27,850 --> 00:02:31,100
the trail of corpses reaches paradise.

26
00:03:10,180 --> 00:03:13,560
Thank you, Einar

27
00:03:15,020 --> 00:03:16,650
and Thorfinn.

28
00:03:18,690 --> 00:03:20,320
Thank you.

29
00:05:29,910 --> 00:05:31,370
Hold him down.

30
00:05:53,510 --> 00:05:55,810
Hold him down tightly!

31
00:05:55,890 --> 00:05:58,810
-He's already dead!
-Pass me the hot water!

32
00:05:58,900 --> 00:06:01,110
Just kill me!

33
00:06:01,730 --> 00:06:03,320
Young master…

34
00:06:07,570 --> 00:06:08,740
Young master…

35
00:06:12,950 --> 00:06:14,910
Dad's hands

36
00:06:16,250 --> 00:06:18,000
are gone.

37
00:06:27,920 --> 00:06:29,380
Young master…

38
00:06:30,760 --> 00:06:32,850
My daughter and my family…

39
00:06:33,930 --> 00:06:35,310
Please…

40
00:06:47,110 --> 00:06:48,570
You can't

41
00:06:49,700 --> 00:06:52,490
even slice a pig!

42
00:07:00,670 --> 00:07:01,750
Young master?

43
00:07:09,630 --> 00:07:10,760
Young master!

44
00:07:17,100 --> 00:07:19,310
Are you okay, young master?

45
00:07:20,100 --> 00:07:22,270
Are you hurt somewhere too?

46
00:07:24,860 --> 00:07:26,020
Your stomach?

47
00:07:26,940 --> 00:07:28,230
Does your stomach hurt?

48
00:07:29,990 --> 00:07:32,070
You should lie down.

49
00:07:45,590 --> 00:07:49,090
We just received
a second summons to surrender.

50
00:07:49,800 --> 00:07:53,760
We can call a truce only if
the entire Ketil family surrenders.

51
00:07:54,470 --> 00:07:57,600
The punishment of outlawry
has not changed.

52
00:07:59,430 --> 00:08:04,190
Choose whether to continue fighting
or to surrender.

53
00:08:04,270 --> 00:08:06,650
That's ridiculous!

54
00:08:07,230 --> 00:08:10,610
I am not going to be
banished from this country!

55
00:08:10,690 --> 00:08:13,910
Do you expect me to leave this land
and become a beggar?

56
00:08:13,990 --> 00:08:18,410
Snake, all of this is happening
because you were incompetent.

57
00:08:19,740 --> 00:08:22,410
You freeloader!

58
00:08:24,500 --> 00:08:28,670
-Boss! You old hag…
-Stop, Fox.

59
00:08:30,380 --> 00:08:34,300
If we say that we'll continue fighting,
what will you do, Snake?

60
00:08:36,590 --> 00:08:38,050
I'll stick around.

61
00:08:41,180 --> 00:08:42,680
That's what I want to hear!

62
00:08:43,390 --> 00:08:46,440
Don't worry, Mother. Leave it up to me.

63
00:08:46,980 --> 00:08:51,570
Twenty people is enough to kill the king.

64
00:08:54,030 --> 00:08:56,950
When you beat a larger army
with a small force,

65
00:08:57,030 --> 00:08:59,330
that's when a man really shines!

66
00:09:00,120 --> 00:09:02,200
Calm down, Thorgil.

67
00:09:02,750 --> 00:09:05,540
You are not the one
who gets to make that decision.

68
00:09:07,330 --> 00:09:08,830
Of course it's me.

69
00:09:08,920 --> 00:09:13,970
Dad is unconscious.
Or did you want to make the decision?

70
00:09:14,720 --> 00:09:16,550
It's not me either.

71
00:09:17,430 --> 00:09:22,600
As the head of the family,
Ketil has chosen an heir.

72
00:09:49,580 --> 00:09:51,250
Surrender.

73
00:09:52,170 --> 00:09:55,170
What are you saying, child?

74
00:09:55,260 --> 00:09:58,090
You should be ashamed as a Nordic man!

75
00:10:04,640 --> 00:10:05,850
I'm ashamed.

76
00:10:06,890 --> 00:10:08,230
I'm ashamed but…

77
00:10:10,350 --> 00:10:11,730
I'm scared.

78
00:10:12,860 --> 00:10:15,070
I'm scared.

79
00:10:15,900 --> 00:10:20,240
I'm scared of seeing others die
and scared of dying myself.

80
00:10:21,450 --> 00:10:23,620
I don't care if we're banished.

81
00:10:24,410 --> 00:10:25,620
I just want

82
00:10:26,250 --> 00:10:28,250
to end all of this.

83
00:10:30,210 --> 00:10:35,590
Don't be ridiculous, Olmar.
You wanted to go to war.

84
00:10:35,670 --> 00:10:38,880
You started this battle
in the first place.

85
00:10:40,050 --> 00:10:42,850
That's right. It's my fault.

86
00:10:43,510 --> 00:10:49,100
I messed up and was ridiculed
and lost my temper and was full of myself.

87
00:10:51,400 --> 00:10:53,860
I'm sorry I did this to all of you.

88
00:10:54,690 --> 00:10:56,730
But because I started this,

89
00:10:57,780 --> 00:11:00,320
I want to be the one to end this.

90
00:11:03,530 --> 00:11:07,500
Look, I'm sorry. I didn't mean that.

91
00:11:08,330 --> 00:11:11,790
They had their eyes on this farm
from the beginning.

92
00:11:12,750 --> 00:11:16,710
But I gave them the opportunity
to start a war.

93
00:11:17,880 --> 00:11:22,510
They can find any reason
to start a war regardless.

94
00:11:22,590 --> 00:11:25,260
If it hadn't been you,
they would've used me or Dad.

95
00:11:26,100 --> 00:11:28,640
You protected your honor back there.

96
00:11:29,390 --> 00:11:34,270
Right, Olmar? You did good.
Honor is more important than life.

97
00:11:35,230 --> 00:11:39,570
Show your courage
as a Nordic warrior once more.

98
00:11:40,860 --> 00:11:41,900
No!

99
00:11:45,570 --> 00:11:48,870
That wasn't courage at all!

100
00:11:50,080 --> 00:11:53,670
<i>I messed up in front of the king.</i>

101
00:11:54,830 --> 00:11:58,210
<i>I'm a stupid, useless man</i>
<i>who deserves to be laughed at.</i>

102
00:11:58,960 --> 00:12:00,210
<i>And yet…</i>

103
00:12:02,840 --> 00:12:04,390
And yet…

104
00:12:06,850 --> 00:12:10,640
I didn't have the courage

105
00:12:11,680 --> 00:12:14,100
to let people laugh at me.

106
00:12:22,150 --> 00:12:26,450
I can't become like you.

107
00:12:27,320 --> 00:12:30,040
I don't care about the honor
of a Nordic warrior.

108
00:12:32,830 --> 00:12:34,370
I will surrender.

109
00:12:35,540 --> 00:12:37,330
Laugh if you want to.

110
00:12:49,810 --> 00:12:53,230
The acting family head
has made a decision.

111
00:12:53,930 --> 00:12:58,310
Olmar, go and tell King Canute
your decision.

112
00:13:03,990 --> 00:13:05,530
I will go with you.

113
00:13:11,950 --> 00:13:15,160
I won't laugh, young master.

114
00:13:20,630 --> 00:13:22,090
I'm over this.

115
00:13:24,470 --> 00:13:25,970
Move out of my way.

116
00:13:27,550 --> 00:13:31,600
-Wait! Where are you going, Thorgil?
-Shut up.

117
00:13:32,260 --> 00:13:34,560
Bye, you cowards.

118
00:13:48,740 --> 00:13:55,200
It may be true that your power
has supported many people.

119
00:13:56,710 --> 00:14:00,630
But I'm sure you have seen
with your own eyes,

120
00:14:01,710 --> 00:14:07,470
what happens to those who become
obsessed with wealth and power.

121
00:14:12,390 --> 00:14:16,560
But it's not like you are
losing everything for nothing.

122
00:14:19,100 --> 00:14:21,230
In exchange for the farm,

123
00:14:22,060 --> 00:14:25,900
your son has become a real man.

124
00:14:36,500 --> 00:14:37,410
<i>Why?</i>

125
00:14:38,210 --> 00:14:39,920
Why did you let him go?

126
00:14:40,670 --> 00:14:44,800
You have been searching for Thorfinn
this whole time, right?

127
00:14:44,880 --> 00:14:49,720
You came all the way here to take
Thorfinn back to your homeland, right?

128
00:14:51,930 --> 00:14:55,470
That is true. That vow I made

129
00:14:55,560 --> 00:14:58,520
has been my reason to live up until now.

130
00:14:59,230 --> 00:15:04,270
No matter how many times I lost
sight of it, I kept searching.

131
00:15:07,150 --> 00:15:09,530
I cannot break my vow to my friend.

132
00:15:10,910 --> 00:15:16,200
But right now, something much bigger
is moving Thorfinn to take action.

133
00:15:17,410 --> 00:15:20,750
And he told me that he will return.

134
00:15:22,210 --> 00:15:25,420
I will trust that look in his eyes.

135
00:15:29,760 --> 00:15:30,930
Thorfinn!

136
00:15:56,620 --> 00:16:02,000
So you're not a member
of the Ketil family?

137
00:16:03,420 --> 00:16:06,460
My name is Thorfinn, son of Thors.

138
00:16:07,170 --> 00:16:09,510
I work as a hand on this farm.

139
00:16:10,590 --> 00:16:13,130
I am here on behalf of Ketil.

140
00:16:14,010 --> 00:16:15,760
Please let me speak with the king.

141
00:16:16,640 --> 00:16:19,520
A hand? You're a slave, aren't you?

142
00:16:22,480 --> 00:16:24,730
I can tell who's a slave right away.

143
00:16:25,400 --> 00:16:27,770
Because they smell like livestock.

144
00:16:33,700 --> 00:16:37,030
You're out of the question.

145
00:16:37,120 --> 00:16:41,540
If the Ketil family doesn't surrender,
we'll just continue the battle.

146
00:16:43,410 --> 00:16:46,670
I am acquainted with the king.

147
00:16:47,210 --> 00:16:49,710
If you tell him my name, he should know.

148
00:16:50,250 --> 00:16:54,010
Please tell him that Thorfinn,
son of Thors, is here.

149
00:17:01,720 --> 00:17:05,480
You and King Canute are acquaintances?

150
00:17:07,400 --> 00:17:10,400
About four years ago,
although it was for a short time,

151
00:17:10,480 --> 00:17:12,860
I served as the king's royal guard.

152
00:17:25,710 --> 00:17:28,040
Did that wake you up, midget?

153
00:17:29,080 --> 00:17:32,960
As if someone as smelly and tiny as you
could be a royal guard!

154
00:17:34,800 --> 00:17:38,760
I apologize if I offended you.
But it is true.

155
00:17:39,390 --> 00:17:41,260
Please tell the king my name.

156
00:17:42,560 --> 00:17:43,640
Please.

157
00:17:44,220 --> 00:17:48,940
What happened, Drott?
That didn't wake him up at all!

158
00:17:49,020 --> 00:17:51,770
Seems like your punch was too weak.

159
00:17:53,980 --> 00:17:55,900
You're not a morning person, huh?

160
00:17:55,990 --> 00:17:58,320
So you want me to wake you up

161
00:17:58,410 --> 00:18:01,700
like your kind little mommy?

162
00:18:03,790 --> 00:18:06,710
Do it!

163
00:18:06,790 --> 00:18:09,210
Come on!

164
00:18:10,630 --> 00:18:13,000
Did you figure out what the fuss is about?

165
00:18:13,090 --> 00:18:16,720
Yes, Ketil has sent over a messenger.

166
00:18:17,340 --> 00:18:19,760
But it is not Ketil himself,

167
00:18:19,840 --> 00:18:22,050
so my men are trying to send him back,

168
00:18:22,600 --> 00:18:25,470
but it seems he is very resilient.

169
00:18:26,640 --> 00:18:29,980
-Did you get his name and status?
-Yes.

170
00:18:30,850 --> 00:18:35,730
He works as a hand on the farm
and is named Thorfinn, son of Thors.

171
00:18:43,120 --> 00:18:44,120
Is he a young

172
00:18:44,790 --> 00:18:46,330
and small man?

173
00:18:47,080 --> 00:18:49,040
Yes, exactly.

174
00:18:50,120 --> 00:18:51,750
Do you know him?

175
00:18:55,340 --> 00:18:56,800
Do it!

176
00:19:00,050 --> 00:19:03,550
What shall we do, Your Majesty?
Would you like to meet him?

177
00:19:07,430 --> 00:19:09,890
No, there is no need for that.

178
00:19:15,230 --> 00:19:17,530
<i>Son of Thors…</i>

179
00:19:18,320 --> 00:19:19,700
<i>There's no way…</i>

180
00:19:20,240 --> 00:19:23,320
-Get him!
-Fight back, midget!

181
00:19:23,410 --> 00:19:24,660
Aim for his eyes!

182
00:19:26,490 --> 00:19:29,120
Wait a second! I don't want to fight you.

183
00:19:32,750 --> 00:19:35,420
Wow, he's pretty agile!

184
00:19:39,300 --> 00:19:41,050
What's wrong, Drott?

185
00:19:41,130 --> 00:19:43,510
-You're not hitting him at all!
-Get it together!

186
00:19:45,970 --> 00:19:48,430
<i>Damn it! I was too naïve.</i>

187
00:19:48,520 --> 00:19:51,020
<i>Anyway, I have to get out of</i>
<i>this situation.</i>

188
00:19:52,020 --> 00:19:55,060
Hurry up and get a punch in, Drott!

189
00:19:55,150 --> 00:19:57,320
The bet is going nowhere.

190
00:20:02,280 --> 00:20:05,950
-Yeah!
-One down!

191
00:20:06,030 --> 00:20:08,950
-Go!
-He's still perfectly fine!

192
00:20:09,040 --> 00:20:11,960
-Kill him!
-Damn it!

193
00:20:13,210 --> 00:20:16,380
-Thorfinn! Are you okay?
-Einar…

194
00:20:17,170 --> 00:20:18,250
Why are you here?

195
00:20:18,340 --> 00:20:21,970
Idiot! Obviously, I'm here to stop you!

196
00:20:23,720 --> 00:20:25,010
I'm sorry.

197
00:20:27,800 --> 00:20:31,020
Just get up already.
Let's hurry up and run.

198
00:20:31,100 --> 00:20:34,310
There's no point in talking to these guys.

199
00:20:34,390 --> 00:20:36,650
All right, pay up.

200
00:20:39,070 --> 00:20:40,320
Thank you.

201
00:20:43,360 --> 00:20:44,400
Thorfinn.

202
00:20:44,990 --> 00:20:47,410
What kind of bet is that?

203
00:20:48,160 --> 00:20:49,950
Huh? Oh…

204
00:20:50,040 --> 00:20:54,370
We're betting on how many punches
it'll take until you run off crying.

205
00:20:54,460 --> 00:20:56,920
Including whether you die
or get knocked out.

206
00:20:57,710 --> 00:21:00,420
The most popular bet is under ten punches.

207
00:21:00,500 --> 00:21:03,800
A few have put their bet on
more than 20 punches.

208
00:21:04,380 --> 00:21:06,390
Come on, you can do it.

209
00:21:06,470 --> 00:21:09,050
-Just one more punch.
-Endure ten more!

210
00:21:10,220 --> 00:21:12,060
Unbelievable!

211
00:21:13,770 --> 00:21:14,810
That bet…

212
00:21:15,600 --> 00:21:17,350
I will join too.

213
00:21:17,900 --> 00:21:20,070
I'll bet on myself.

214
00:21:22,860 --> 00:21:25,570
Even if I win, I don't need the money.

215
00:21:25,650 --> 00:21:26,820
In return,

216
00:21:28,780 --> 00:21:31,660
you will let me speak with the king.

217
00:21:36,500 --> 00:21:38,290
Did you hear that?

218
00:21:38,380 --> 00:21:40,960
That midget just said something
really interesting.

219
00:21:42,380 --> 00:21:45,550
All right, why not? You've got guts.

220
00:21:45,630 --> 00:21:49,800
But I won't let you bet
on under ten punches.

221
00:21:51,720 --> 00:21:54,020
What has nobody bet on yet?

222
00:21:54,100 --> 00:21:55,770
Let's see…

223
00:21:55,850 --> 00:21:58,980
There are bets all the way up to 90.

224
00:22:00,400 --> 00:22:02,860
Then 100 punches it is.

225
00:22:02,940 --> 00:22:05,860
If you endure 100 punches, you win.

226
00:22:06,610 --> 00:22:09,870
If you lose, we will take your life.

227
00:22:11,280 --> 00:22:13,830
-Very well.
-Hey!

228
00:22:15,200 --> 00:22:18,460
Thorfinn! Why would you go

229
00:22:18,540 --> 00:22:21,080
that far just for Ketil?

230
00:22:21,790 --> 00:22:24,050
This is war.

231
00:22:24,130 --> 00:22:26,300
A single person can't do
anything about it.

232
00:22:26,840 --> 00:22:30,720
If they want to fight,
just let them fight amongst themselves.

233
00:22:33,350 --> 00:22:34,720
I…

234
00:22:35,890 --> 00:22:38,100
am glad that

235
00:22:39,190 --> 00:22:41,230
I ended up on this farm.

236
00:22:42,730 --> 00:22:45,780
<i>I didn't know anything other than war,</i>

237
00:22:46,860 --> 00:22:48,780
<i>but the master, Pater,</i>

238
00:22:49,740 --> 00:22:50,610
<i>and the old master</i>

239
00:22:51,620 --> 00:22:52,780
<i>didn't give up on me.</i>

240
00:22:53,620 --> 00:22:54,950
<i>They were good to me.</i>

241
00:22:56,950 --> 00:22:58,750
<i>I even got to meet you.</i>

242
00:23:02,330 --> 00:23:05,460
I know you agree with me, deep down.

243
00:23:06,880 --> 00:23:08,340
Are you okay with never

244
00:23:09,130 --> 00:23:12,010
being able to pay back the kindness
you were shown?

245
00:23:18,520 --> 00:23:21,020
-Thorfinn…
-It's fine, Einar.

246
00:23:23,110 --> 00:23:25,070
There's a trick to being punched.

247
00:23:26,070 --> 00:23:28,690
I am used to being punched.

248
00:23:29,490 --> 00:23:32,860
-Are you serious?
-Way to go!

249
00:23:32,950 --> 00:23:35,200
Take down that blockhead!

250
00:23:37,490 --> 00:23:39,410
He's making a fool out of you, Drott!

251
00:23:40,250 --> 00:23:42,170
Are you all show?

252
00:23:42,790 --> 00:23:44,880
Just squash him already!

253
00:23:46,290 --> 00:23:49,210
I, Drott the Bear Killer,

254
00:23:49,800 --> 00:23:52,930
have never been humiliated
like this before!

255
00:23:55,140 --> 00:23:56,930
I will kill you.

256
00:23:57,890 --> 00:24:00,640
Is he stupid? He's going to die!

257
00:24:00,730 --> 00:24:03,060
Try to last until 20 punches!

258
00:24:03,150 --> 00:24:04,600
Get him!

259
00:25:53,090 --> 00:25:55,050
<i>"Emperor of Rebellion."</i>

260
00:25:55,130 --> 00:25:56,930
Subtitle translation by: Kiko Morita

